text: Linn County is a county in the U.S. state of Iowa. As of the 2020 census, the population was 230,299, making it the second-most populous county in Iowa. The county seat is Cedar Rapids. The county was founded on January 15, 1839 and named in honor of Senator Lewis F. Linn of Missouri. == References == Category:1830s establishments in Iowa Territory Category:1839 establishments in the United States Category:Iowa counties
